<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;text-align:center;'><strong><span style="font-size:20px;line-height:107%;">Continuous Integration Using Jenkins, Nexus, SonarQube, Slack</span></strong></p>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong><u>Benefits</u></strong></p>
<p style='margin:0in;font-size:15px;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>Short MTTR - Mean Time To Repair</p>
<p style='margin:0in;font-size:15px;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>Fault Isolation</p>
<p style='margin:0in;font-size:15px;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>Agile</p>
<p style='margin:0in;font-size:15px;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>No Human Intervention Required</p>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>&nbsp;</p>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong><u>Tools used&nbsp;</u></strong></p>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>Jenkins, GIT, Maven, Checkstyle, Slack, Sonatype Nexus, Sonarqube, AWS EC2</p>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong><u>Goals Achieved</u></strong></p>
<p style='margin:0in;font-size:15px;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>Fast TAT on Feature changes</p>
<p style='margin:0in;font-size:15px;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>Less Disruptive</p>
<p style='margin:0in;font-size:15px;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>&nbsp;</p>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong><u>Workflow</u></strong></p>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>The below flowchart illustrates, how the code passes through every stage.</p>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>&nbsp;<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," style="width: 451.5pt; height: 315.75pt;" alt="image"></p>
<ol style="list-style-type: decimal;">
    <li>Developers Commits the Code into GIT(Source Code Management). This application is built on Java, so we are using Maven as build tool.</li>
    <li>Jenkins fetches the code and builds(compiles) it, runs Unit Tests on it and write the outcome as a notification in Slack/Teams</li>
    <li>Next it runs the Code Analysis using Sonarqube and puts the code through Quality Gates and if it passes the quality thresholds it will send the notification to Slack/Teams</li>
    <li>If it is not passing the quality thresholds - It will be passed to Developer to fix the bugs and the process begins from scratch</li>
    <li>After passing through Code Analysis, the artifact will be packaged and uploaded to the artifact repository that is Nexus and a notification will be sent through Slack/Teams</li>
</ol>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong><u>Flow of Execution</u></strong></p>

<ol start="2" style="list-style-type: decimal;">
    <li>Clone the Github repository &ndash; ci-jenkins. After cloning, always run &ldquo;git pull&rdquo; to update the latest changes. Switch to the branch &ndash; &ldquo;git checkout ci-jenkins&rdquo;</li>
    <li>Navigate to &ldquo;userdata&rdquo; folder. Shell scripts are available to create the EC2 instances for Jenkins, Nexus and Sonarqube</li>
    <li>Install all roles using Ubuntu 22.04.</li>
    <li>AWS Portal <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> EC2 <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Launch an instance <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Select t2.small (which will have some charges)</li>

Under Advanced Details section <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> User Data <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> fill it with the shell script for nexus from userdata. Repeat the steps 5 and 6 for Jenkins and Sonarqube servers</li>
    <li>Provide proper tags to identify the instances</li>
</ol>

    <li>Access the VM with the public IP address with port 8081. &lt;public ip&gt;:8081</li>
    <li>To sign in, we need to SSH into the Nexus VM with the key file and the default user is &ldquo;admin&rdquo;</li>
    <li>The password is in the file &ldquo;/opt/nexus/sonatype-work/nexus3/admin.password&rdquo;.</li>
    <li>Post installation wizard opens. Follow the instructions to finish the post installation steps.</li>
    <li>We need to create three maven repositories. Administration <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Repository <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Repositories <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Create Repository<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
            <li>Select maven2(hosted) <strong>javaprofile-release&nbsp;</strong>(This repository will have artifacts which are well tested and deployed to servers)</li>
            <li>Select maven2(proxy) <strong>javaprofile-maven-central.&nbsp;</strong>We have provide the remote repository address to download all dependencies<strong>&nbsp;</strong>(This repository will have all the dependencies downloaded from the maven public repository)</li>
        </ol>
    </li>
</ol>

<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>

    <ol start="8" style="margin-bottom:0in;list-style-type: decimal;">
        <li style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>To perform simple code analysis, we have to install a plugin called &ldquo;checkstyle&rdquo;</li>
    </ol>
</div>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<div style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>
    <ol start="9" style="margin-bottom:0in;list-style-type: decimal;">
        <li style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>Manage Jenkins <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Manage Plugins <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Available <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Search for &ldquo;checks&rdquo; <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Select &ldquo;Checkstyle&rdquo; and &ldquo;Violations&rdquo; <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> &ldquo;Install without Restart&rdquo;</li>
    </ol>
</div>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:.5in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<ol start="10" style="list-style-type: decimal;">
    <li>Checkstyle will analyze the code and give the report. If the failures goes beyond threshold defined by quality gates, Violations will make the job unstable, so it won&rsquo;t be promoted to next step.</li>
    <li>Create a job in Jenkins for code analysis. Create new job and copy the settings of build job. For goals, enter &ldquo;checkstyle:checkstyle&rdquo;.</li>
    <li>Configure &ldquo;Post Build Actions&rdquo; <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> &ldquo;Publish Checkstyle analysis results</li>
</ol>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<div style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>

        <li style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'>Run the job and results will be saved in the workspace</li>
    </ol>
</div>
<p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Aptos",sans-serif;'><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<ol start="14" style="list-style-type: decimal;">
    <li>Create a new job as &ldquo;Code_Analysis&rdquo; and copy the settings of &ldquo;Build&rdquo; job</li>
    <li>In &ldquo;Build Environment&rdquo; tab <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Invoke top-level Maven targets <span style="font-family:Wingdings;"><span style="font-family:Wingdings;">&agrave;</span></span> Goals &ldquo;checkstyle:checkstyle&rdquo;</li>
